                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Salt Funds/189: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-15T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 15, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>382. Following for Tokyo: as Department’s 196, June 15, 7 p.m.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Your 378, June 14, 2 p.m.,<note n="7" xml:id="d774fn7">See telegram No. 839,
                            June 14, 6 p.m., from the Consul General at Shanghai, <ref
                                target="#pg_726">p. 726</ref>.</note> Chinese Salt Administration.
                        The Department authorizes you, when you have ascertained that your British
                        colleague is prepared to take similar action, to leave with the Foreign
                        Office an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> referring to your <hi
                            rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of March 19, and stating that the
                        American Government would welcome assurances from the Japanese Government
                        that it is prepared to accord full respect to American interests in the
                        Chinese salt revenues.”<note n="8" xml:id="d774fn8">For American and
                            Japanese exchange of memoranda on June 21 and August: 31, see <ref
                                target="frus1931-41v01#pg_745">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                    rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 745</ref>.</note>
                    </p>
                </quote>
                <p>Repeat to Hankow and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
